<br>
Well, VI eventually forgot their own reasoning and made rangers get uber archery withlittle aggro.<br>
<br>
That brings me back to my warrior...after all this time of intermittent pulling and tagging, archery skill = 238. Bow = 30 damage. Result: &quot;you try to shoot _target, but miss!!&quot; &quot;You have hit _target for 2 points&quot;!!<br>
<br>
I know a 55 ranger with lower skill and same damage bow and almost every shot does double damage.<br>
It almost seems like there is a modifier on warrior archery to make it worse, or maybe they just never changed the code at all. But since a warrior is master of all weapons, and they give us the skill cap of 250, I would like to see the Option of doing bow damage... <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=366288">Quakr's profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wold2>wold2</A> at: 3/19/03 11:54:24 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yaenbzhen>YaenBzhen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/03 11:53:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3039.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   re: Why does warrior archery STILL suck?</span><hr size=1> Before I say anything else, I know the direction people are going to try to respond to this post, so I'm going to answer them before I actually say anything...<br>
<br>
1) I think ranger archery is grossly unbalanced in more than just a couple of ways. Ranger Glade posts about the upcoming archery aggro change are hedging on druidic-levels of whining. With or without obscene range damage, rangers have nothing to whine about.<br>
<br>
2) The original question in this thread didn't have anything to do with ranger archery balance, but rather *warrior* archery and how it compares to rangers.<br>
<br>
That being said, I'll be the first to say that warriors need improvement in a lot of areas, but I don't think archery is one of them. A ranger is, by nature, more adept with the use of a bow, and should accordingly see better performance out of one. The concept of a guy decked out in huge plates of heavy steel running around bow kiting mobs just seems silly to me.<br>
<br>
For that matter, I frankly think it's a little bit unfair to rangers that warriors' archery cap is identical to their own. It would seem logical to me that warriors would have an archery cap adjusted similarly to the way piercing is adjusted against rogues. <br>
<br>
Those two weapons especially are hallmark weapons for other classes, and just because we warriors have slowly had all our class defining attributes stripped away from us and given to others doesn't mean we need to demand those that we didn't (and shouldn't) have.<br>
<br>
Yaen B`zhen<br>
Overlord of the Lightbearer<br>
Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=varaho1>Varaho1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1429<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/03 12:12:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3039.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   why?</span><hr size=1> Our archery sucks 'cause of a few things:<br>
<br>
1: No double/triple attack ( this hurts allot )<br>
<br>
2: No damage bonus ( again this hurts allot )<br>
<br>
3: Skill cap ( this has an effect, but not even in the same ballpark as the other two )<br>
<br>
So its not because we have a penalty but rather we have no bonuses that archery does so little damage.<br>
